[[File:Chateau-Domecy-2.JPG|thumb|Château de Domecy-sur-Cure (2012)]]
The '''Château de Domecy-sur-Cure''' is a [[château]] located in [[Domecy-sur-Cure]] in the [[Yonne]] [[Departments of France|department]] in [[Burgundy]], north-central [[France]].

The date of its construction goes back to the 15th century. Various renovation work and extensions took place in the 17th century. Inside the fireplace in the main room dates to the Renaissance. It was inscribed as a [[monument historique]] in March 1986.<ref>http://www.culture.gouv.fr/public/mistral/merimee_fr?ACTION=CHERCHER&FIELD_1=REF&VALUE_1=PA00113674</ref>

The château is still privately owned.

