[[File:THIS MAN IS YOUR FRIEND. ETHIOPIAN - NARA - 515794.jpg|thumb|An American propaganda poster during the [[Second World War]] depicting a bugler from the band.]] The '''Ethiopian National Defence Force Band (ENDFB)''' ([[Amharic]]: የኢትዮጵያ ብሔራዊ መከላከያ ባንድ) is a musical division in the [[Ethiopian National Defense Force]]. The band is the successor to the [[Imperial Bodyguard Band]] for the [[Ethiopian Empire]]. It commonly receives assistance from the British [[Corps of Army Music]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://britisharmy.wordpress.com/2014/04/11/army-music-making-in-ethiopia/amp/|title=Army music making in Ethiopia|website=|accessdate=2018-07-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://britisharmy.wordpress.com/2013/04/09/short-term-training-for-ethiopian-national-defence-force-band/amp/|title=Short term training for Ethiopian National Defence Force band|website=|accessdate=2018-07-18}}</ref> It is composed of a [[Marching band]], a [[Big band]] and a [[Corps of Drums]]. The band also maintains a youth division.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/20/arts/music/hailu-mergia-lala-belu.html|title=At 10, he moved with his mother to Addis, and a few years later, he joined the Ethiopian Army band’s youth division.|website=The New York Times|accessdate=2018-07-18}}</ref>
