'''Gwarsum''' was a 19th-century leader of the [[Ningi chiefdom]]. Little is known about him, but from around 1807 he looked to increase the size of his chiefdom in the area that is now Butawa Territory. He was known to have secured a victory over the [[Emir of Kano]], [[Ibrahim Dabo]], which affected relations in the area and caused numerous conflicts.<ref name="Kopytoff1987">{{cite book|last=Kopytoff|first=Igor|title=The African frontier: the reproduction of traditional African societies|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Mt4OAQAAMAAJ|accessdate=1 November 2011|year=1987|publisher=Indiana University Press|isbn=978-0-253-30252-6|pages=198–9}}</ref>

After his death he was succeeded by his son [[Tunsuru]] and then his other son [[Garta]].<ref name="Patton1975">{{cite book|last=Patton|first=Adell|title=The Ningi chiefdom and the African frontier: mountaineers and resistance to the Sokoto Caliphate ca. 1800-1908|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=85UPAQAAMAAJ|accessdate=1 November 2011|year=1975|publisher=University of Wisconsin|page=77}}</ref>

