{{Infobox Newspaper |name = L'Esportiu |image = |caption = |type = Daily [[newspaper]] |format = |ceased publication = |price = [[Euro]]1 |foundation = 2 January 2002 |owners = |language = [[Catalan language|Catalan]] |political = |circulation = |headquarters = Tàpies 2, [[Barcelona]] |editor = |website = [http://www.lesportiudecatalunya.cat/ lesportiudecatalunya.cat] }}
'''''L'Esportiu''''', previously known as '''''El 9 Esportiu''''' ({{IPA-ca|əl ˈnɔw əspuɾˈtiw}}), is a [[Catalan language|Catalan]] daily [[sport]]s [[newspaper]], based in [[Barcelona]], [[Catalonia]].
==History== The newspaper was founded on 2 January 2002, being the unique [[Catalan language]] daily [[sport]]s [[newspaper]]. In addition to selling individual, is also included in several newspapers as ''[[El punt|El Punt]]'', ''[[Segre (newspaper)|Segre]]'', ''[[Regió 7]]'' and ''[[Diari d'Andorra]]''.
''El 9 esportiu'' offers three editions customized for [[Girona]], [[Barcelona]] and [[Tarragona]], which include all the information from the elite sport and sport for each local area. These editions are distributed in conjunction with the corresponding edition of the newspaper ''[[El punt|El Punt]]''.
In 2003, was awarded with the National Award for the Social Projection of the Catalan language, granted by the [[Generalitat de Catalunya|Catalan government]], in recognition of being "the first sports daily in catalan, which has contributed to the consolidation and growth of Catalan language in sport".
