'''Luxinnovation''' is an organisation that contributes to the economic development of [[Luxembourg]] by fostering innovation, fuelling international growth and attracting foreign direct investment.
Luxinnovation’s mission is to strengthen national business through innovation and to promote Luxembourg business abroad (import-export). This we do by focussing on impact and generating real client value.
== History == Founded in 1984, Luxinnovation is an Economic Interest Grouping (EIG) that, since 1998, has combined the efforts of: * the Ministry of the Economy * the Ministry for Higher Education and Research * the Luxembourg Chamber of Commerce * the Chambre des Métiers * Fedil
== Startup support == In an effort to foster the local entrepreneurial ecosystem in the technological field, in 2015 Luxinnovation launched its first startup accelerator [[Fit for Start]], that offers a grant of €50.000 equity free to selected projects operating in the ICT.<ref>{{cite web|title=FIT4START: LAUNCH OF A NEW STATE SUPPORT PROGRAMME FOR ICT START-UPS|url=http://www.luxembourgforfinance.com/en/news/fit4start-launch-new-state-support-programme-ict-start-ups|website=luxembourgforfinance.com|publisher=luxembourgforfinance|accessdate=15 June 2018}}</ref>
