'''Martin Collins''' is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[radio presenter]]. He started broadcasting as soon as he left college.  His broadcasting career began at [[Chiltern FM|Chiltern Radio]]. Next, he moved to London's [[Capital London|Capital Radio]], first presenting a Sunday night specialist show for the station, before moving to prominence on the latenight show (10{{nbsp}}pm{{snd}}1{{nbsp}}am) in 1986{{ndash}}1989. He later moved to the weekday afternoon slot before eventually leaving the station in December 2003.

At the beginning of 2004, Collins went 'freelance', heard on various stations across the UK such as [[Virgin Radio]], [[Magic 105.4]] and [[Capital Gold]]. In July 2004, Martin joined [[Virgin Radio]] on a permanent basis, with stints on drivetime and the late show, leaving the station in December 2006. He replaced [[Russell Pockett]] on drivetime when [[102.2 Smooth Radio]] relaunched in early 2007, and remained in the slot until December 2008.

Collins has most recently been heard covering the late show on [[The One Network]] and various programmes on [[Absolute Radio]] and Magic 105.4 London. In late 2009, he took on the weekend breakfast show (6{{snd}}10{{nbsp}}am) on Magic 105.4, then he presented various shows like Early Breakfast, Weekday Mellow Magic and just before he left the station he presented Magic Weekend Afternoons (Saturday and Sunday 3{{snd}}6{{nbsp}}pm) until late September 2016. Since October Tom Price took over presenting Magic Weekend Afternoons (Saturday 3{{snd}}6{{nbsp}}pm and Sunday 1{{snd}}4{{nbsp}}pm) until August 2017. From September 2017, Tom Price started hosting Weekend Breakfast on Magic. Matt Brown can now be heard every weekend afternoons on Magic Radio. 

Martin moved back to [[Smooth Radio]] in 2017 part of [[Global Radio]]. He presents weekend editions of ''Smooth Late show'' from 10{{nbsp}}pm to 1{{nbsp}}am on Smooth Radio just like Danny Pietroni who presents this show's weekday editions on Smooth Radio. Alongside his weekend late night shift, he is also a weekday freelance presenter on the network.

